15:
Don't worry about me! Now's your
chance!
26:
What was that woman wielding... A
magical device? At any rate...
28:
Don't let those criminals get away!
After them!
30:
Commander, should we move out
as well?
33:
No, it's fine. We can leave the rest to
the local troops.
36:
We should check on the citizens.
Administer first aid to any injured
and reestablish order in town.
50:
Take this chance to treat the
wounded! We'll move out as soon as
everyone's patched up!
54:
Rashid. I object to your behavior
earlier. Why did you protect me from
the soldier?
58:
No particular reason. I just did what
anyone else would do—stepped in
when I saw one of my comrades in
danger.
62:
You are mistaken. I am a weapon. It
is illogical to endanger yourself to
save a tool.
66:
Hey, now. It's true that I rely on your
powers in a pinch, but there's no
need to call yourself a tool.
69: It just... rubs me the wrong way.
77:
Haha, you can complain to me all
you want later. First we have to get
ourselves out of this mess.
81:
We'll head for our hideout while
avoiding any pursuers. What will you
folks do?
86:
We'll stick with you until these
people are safe.
90:
That soldier—Haridal, I believe you
called him... He was quite the
handful.
94:
Yeah, he's always been really skilled
with a blade...
98: He an old friend of yours then?
102:
My best friend, even... We grew up
together.
105:
Did everything together. Swore we'd
one day free the borderlands.
108:
He and I actually formed the Golden
Dawn. Built it from the ground up.
116:
Wait, Haridal! What do you mean
you're leaving the Golden Dawn?
118:
...I'm not like you. I don't have the
patience to stop and help every
person weaker than me.
119: I'll free the borderlands my way.
125:
Still, I never thought he'd end up
joining the kingdom.
128:
Maybe I didn't know him as well as I
thought I did...
132:
You never know. Could be he's got a
reason for it.
136:
Could be. But none of this changes
anything. I still have to forge my own
path ahead.
139:
Do what I can to make a difference...
Including patching up our wounded!
147:
Appreciate it. The sooner we finish,
the sooner we can get going.
153:
Excuse me. May I have a moment of
your time?
156:
Oh, Haridal! Of course, of course. You
come at a good time. I was just
thinking of sending for you to offer a
word of thanks.
157:
I heard you spared no effort in
quelling the unrest earlier.
159:
I simply did my duty as a
commander in service of the
kingdom.
161:
Haha, an admirable devotion to
duty. If only more of my people
would follow your example. Truly,
you act beyond what one would
expect of a commoner.
163:
Not that there aren't naysayers.
Some of them even claim your true
origins to be the borderlands... I
hope they haven't given you too
much trouble.
166:
No matter how I protest, there will
always be those opposed to me.
168:
However, I shall prove my worth
through actions instead.
171:
My troops and I will take care of the
Golden Dawn and put an end to
their crimes.
